    "reasoning": "The task requires finding the minimum of four 8-bit unsigned numbers using combinational logic. We can compare pairs of numbers and propagate the smallest result until we get the final minimum. This approach avoids the complexity of using state machines or flip-flops for this simple problem. The initial values for the intermediate comparisons are set to the maximum possible value, which ensures that the first valid comparison will overwrite these initial values.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    logic [7:0] a,\n    logic [7:0] b,\n    logic [7:0] c,\n    logic [7:0] d,\n    logic [7:0] min\n);\n\n    // Intermediate comparisons\n    logic [7:0] comp1;\n    logic [7:0] comp2;\n    logic [7:0] comp3;\n\n    // Initialize intermediate results to the maximum value\n    initial begin\n        comp1 = 8'hFF;\n        comp2 = 8'hFF;\n        comp3 = 8'hFF;\n    end\n\n    // Compare a and b\n    assign comp1 = (a < b) ? a : b;\n\n    // Compare c and d\n    assign comp2 = (c < d) ? c : d;\n\n    // Compare the results of the previous comparisons\n    assign comp3 = (comp1 < comp2) ? comp1 : comp2;\n\n    // Assign the final result to min\n    assign min = comp3;\n\nendmodule"
}
